sentence: Looking at options trading activity among components of the S&P 500 index, there is noteworthy activity today in CF Industries Holdings Inc (Symbol: CF), where a total volume of 12,887 contracts has been traded thus far today, a contract volume which is representative of approximately 1.3 million underlying shares (given that every 1 contract represents 100 underlying shares).
That number works out to 43.1% of CF's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 3.0 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $41 strike call option expiring February 16, 2018 , with 1,605 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 160,500 underlying shares of CF.

That number of contracts represents approximately 1.1 million underlying shares, working out to a sizeable 42.7% of WM's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 2.6 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $82.50 strike call option expiring February 16, 2018 , with 1,096 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 109,600 underlying shares of WM.
